=head1 TEST PROCEDURE

=begin html
<PRE>
                    
      LFN0    NUTX     HA0     HA1      R1      R2     CN0
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        |       | <-------------------- |       |       | 1.Router Advertisement
        |       |       |       |       |       |       | 
        |       | ----> |       |       |       |       | 2.Binding Update
        |       | <---- |       |       |       |       | 3.Binding Acknowledgement
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        |       | ----> |       |       |       |       | 4.Home Agent Address Discovery Request
        |       | <---- |       |       |       |       | 5.Home Agent Address Discovery Reply
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        |       | ----> |       |       |       |       | 6.Binding Update (*1)
        |       | <---- |       |       |       |       | 7.Binding Acknowledgement
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        |       | ------------> |       |       |       | 8.Binding Update (*2)
        |       | <------------ |       |       |       | 9.Binding Acknowledgement
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        |       | <------------ |       |       |       | 10.ICMP Echo Request
        |       | ------------> |       |       |       | 11.ICMP Echo Reply (*3)
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
        | <---- | <============ | <-------------------- | 12.ICMP Echo Request (*4)
        | ----> | ============> | --------------------> | 13.ICMP Echo Reply (*5)
        |       |       |       |       |       |       |
                    
        1. Send Router Advertisement. (R1 -> R1_allnode_multi)
        2. Receive Binding Update. (NUTX -> HA0)
            # The Mobile Router (R) bit is set to 1.
        3. Send Binding Acknowledgement. (HA0 -> NUTX)
            # The Status field is set to 1(accepted but prefix discovery necessary).
            # The Mobile Router (R) bit is set to 0.
        4. Receive Home Agent Address Discovery Request. (NUTX -> NUTX_ha_any)
            # The Mobile Router Support Flag (R) bit is set to 1.
        5. Send Home Agent Address Discovery Reply. (HA0 -> NUTX)
            # The Home Agent Addresses field contains global IP address for HA1.
            # The Mobile Router Support Flag (R) bit is set to 1.
        6. Receive Binding Update. (NUTX -> HA0)
            # The Lifetime field is set to 0.
        7. Send Binding Acknowledgement. (HA0 -> NUTX)
        8. Receive Binding Update. (NUTX -> HA1)
            # The Mobile Router (R) bit is set to 1.
        9. Send Binding Acknowledgement. (HA1 -> NUTX)
            # The Mobile Router (R) bit is set to 1.
       10. Send ICMP Echo Request. (HA1 -> NUTX with Type2 Routing Header)
       11. Receive ICMP Echo Reply. (NUTX -> HA1 with Home Address Option)
       12. Send ICMP Echo Request. (out: HA1 -> NUTX, in: CN0 -> LFN0)
            Receive ICMP Echo Request. (CN0 -> LFN0)
       13. Send ICMP Echo Reply. (LFN0 -> CN0)
            Receive ICMP Echo Reply. (out: NUTX -> HA1, in: LFN0 -> CN0)
                    
    Focus Packet Format:
        <A HREF="../images/NEMO_Binding_Update_message_format_ESP_Imp_from_MR_to_HA.gif">6. Binding Update</A>
</PRE>

=end html

=head1 JUDGEMENT

=begin html
<PRE>
 (*1) PASS: HA0 receives Binding Update.
            Then, check whether this packet fills all of the following.
             - The Lifetime field is set to 0. 
 (*2) PASS: HA1 receives Binding Update.
            Then, check whether this packet fills all of the following,
            - The Mobile Router Flag (R) is set to 1.
 (*3) PASS: HA1 receives ICMP Echo Reply with Home Address Option.
 (*4) PASS: LFN0 receives ICMP Echo Request.
 (*5) PASS: CN0 receives ICMP Echo Reply.
                    
                    
</PRE>

=end html

